24/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Supreme Cassation Prosecution (SCP) presented a report Tuesday (23 November) on its activities against organised crime during the first nine months of the year. According to SCP data, as of the end of September, a total of 308 people were charged with involvement in organised crime, while 123 were sentenced by the court. Since the start of the year, prosecutors have launched 1,138 probes into organised crime cases. The report underscored the need for urgent adoption of the bill on confiscating property gained as a result of illegal activity, in order to strengthen institutional mechanisms for crime fighting. (Mediapool, Nova TV - 23/11/04)
